    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - REMOVE - RIGHT REVERSE IDLER GEAR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>RIGHT REVERSE IDLER GEAR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use curved pry bar to walk bearing from the idler bore in the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302443">Figure 43</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302443" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302443" filename="../figg13/G1302443.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 43. Use Pry Bar to Walk Bearing From Idler Bore in Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear idler washer and holder from the bore. If necessary, bend holder lugs and
                remove the washer from the holder.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse idler gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302444">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302444" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302444" filename="../figg13/G1302444.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 44. Remove Reverse Idler Gear From Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the idler bearing from the reverse idler gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front idler washer from the case.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
